GymMachines.MachineDescription: Leg presses are seated exercises done on a leg press machine. To start, sit with your back against a padded backrest and your feet on two large footrests. Your knees are bent to start the exercise. To move the weight, you must straighten your legs and then return them to the bent position.

The machine chest press is a machine-based exercise targeting the chest. It approximates the motion of a bench press but is usually performed facing forward and seated upright. Many machines offer multiple grip options, such as overhand, neutral (palms facing), or underhand.
